1 AN ACT concerning crimes, punishment and criminal procedure; relating
2 to crimes involving government functions; creating the crimes of
3 interference with a security camera in a correctional facility and
4 aggravated interference with a security camera in a correctional facility
5 and providing criminal penalties therefor.
6
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
8 Section 1. (a) Interference with a security camera in a correctional
9 facility is intentionally covering a security camera in a correctional facility
10 without authority from the correctional facility.
11 (b) Aggravated interference with a security camera in a correctional
12 facility is intentionally:
13 (1) Removing, damaging or rendering inoperable a security camera in
14 a correctional facility without authority from the correctional facility; or
15 (2) covering, removing, damaging or rendering inoperable a security
16 camera in a correctional facility during a riot at the correctional facility
17 without authority from the correctional facility.
18 (c) (1) Interference with a security camera in a correctional facility is
19 a class A nonperson misdemeanor; and
20 (2) aggravated interference with a security camera in a correctional
21 facility as defined in:
22 (A) Subsection (b)(1) is a severity level 9, nonperson felony; and
23 (B) subsection (b)(2) is a severity level 6, nonperson felony.
24 (d) As used in this section:
25 (1) "Correctional facility" means a:
26 (A) Jail or correctional facility operated by a city, county or
27 consolidated law enforcement agency;
28 (B) correctional institution as defined in K.S.A. 75-5202, and
29 amendments thereto; or
30 (C) juvenile detention facility as defined in K.S.A. 38-2302, and
31 amendments thereto; and
32 (2) "security camera" means an analog or digital photographic or
33 video camera or other device capable of recording or transmitting a
34 photograph, motion picture or other digital image.
35 (e) This section shall be a part of and supplemental to the Kansas
36 criminal code.

